The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Designer attacked

 New Delhi, Aug. 12 (PTI): A fashion designer was attacked yesterday by two men who doused her with kerosene and threw a lighted matchstick.

 Darvin Suri was assaulted outside her home in the upscale Greater Kailash II area.

 Her mother-in-law, Kusum, who was also injured, said: Two men fled on a motorbike. The family said Darvin has been getting threat calls over the past few days and was attacked four days back.

 Darvin suffered 80 per cent burns and is in Safdarjung Hospital.




